A vintage 1950s advertisement style illustration of a frustrated man in a retro living room, tangled in a chaotic web of copper telephone wires and coaxial cables that spiral outward from the walls like overgrown vines. The man sits in a mid-century modern armchair, arms crossed, eyebrow raised skeptically. On a side table, an old rotary phone sits next to a primitive modem with blinking lights. Through the window, a gleaming futuristic city skyline promises technological advancement just out of reach. The color palette features muted teals, mustard yellows, and salmon pinks typical of 1950s commercial art, with halftone dot patterns and slightly faded edges giving it an authentic aged magazine advertisement quality.
